724986f-a.text:
150-74 6th Avenue, south side, between 150th Street, and Powells Cove Boulevard, Whitestone, showing the new armory of the Fourth Battalion New York Naval Militia, erected by the Works Progress Administration. For additional data see The New York Times, Sept. 27, 1937, page 23, report of Colonel Somervell.
Federal Art Project -- W.P.A.  October, 1936
Photographic Division
